        <heading>2578.  Liability for deterioration at the time of redemption</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 2578.  Liability for deterioration at the time of redemption
During the time allowed for redemption, the buyer must administer the thing sold with the degree of care of a prudent administrator.  He is liable to the redeeming seller for any deterioration of the thing caused by the lack of such care.</p>
        </content>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=109632</p>
